addValidator(address,bool,address).details: Add a new validator to the contract.

params.feeRecipient: Address of the fee recipient. false when adding the validator to the second committee.
params.isFirstCommittee: True when adding the validator to the first committee.

approveExecute(uint256,address,uint256,a.details: Approve and/or execute a given request.

params.to: Address to release the funds to.

attesters(bytes32).details: Returns the number of attesters and their indeces for a given request hash.

claimProtocolFees(address,address).details: Allows the weak-admin to claim the accumulated protocol fees.

params.recipient: Address of the protocol fee recipient.
params.token: Token to claim protocol fees for.

claimValidatorFees(address).details: Allows to claim accumulated fees for a validator.

configureValidatorFeeRecipient(address,a.details: Change fee recipient for a validator.

params.feeRecipient: Address of the new fee recipient.

createAddToken(string,string,address,add.details: Link a token to its mirror token. A new token will be deployed if existingToken is the zero address. Otherwise the existingToken will be used instead, which means that a contract migration is underway.

params.existingToken: Address of an existing wrapped token that will be used instead of deploying a new token. A new token will be deployed if this is set as the zero address.
params.mirrorToken: Address of the token that will be deposited in the mirror contract.
params.tokenName: Name of the token to be created.
params.tokenSymbol: Symbol of the token to be created.

returns.token: Address of the new wrap token.

deposit(address,uint256,address).details: Deposit tokens to bridge to the other side.

params.to: Address to release the tokens to on the other side.

returns.id: The ID associated to the request.

forceSetNextExecutionIndex(uint256).details: Forcefully set next next execution index.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

migrate(address).details: Migrates the contract to a new address.

nextExecutionIndex().details: Returns the index of the request that will be executed next.

removeValidator(address).details: Remove existing validator from the contract.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

validatorInfo(address).details: Returns info about a given validator.

addValidator(address,bool,address).notice: Can only be called by the admin.

claimProtocolFees(address,address).notice: Can only be called by the weak-admin.

claimValidatorFees(address).notice: Can be triggered by anyone but the fee is transfered to the set feeRecepient for the validator.

configureMultisig((uint8,uint8)).notice: Can only be called by the admin.

configureProtocolFees(uint16).notice: Can only be called by the weak-admin.

configureToken(address,(uint256,uint256,.notice: Set maxAmount to zero to disable the token.Can only be called by the weak-admin.

configureValidatorFees(uint16).notice: Can only be called by the weak-admin.

createAddToken(string,string,address,add.notice: Set maxAmount to zero to disable the token.Can only be called by the weak-admin.

forceSetNextExecutionIndex(uint256).notice: Can only be called by the admin of the contract.

migrate(address).notice: This function can only be called once in the lifetime of this contract by the admin.

pause().notice: The contract can be paused by all addresses with pause role but can only be unpaused by the weak-admin.

removeValidator(address).notice: Can only be called by the weak-admin.The fees accumulated by the validator are distributed before being removed.

tokens(uint256).notice: A token in the list might not be active.

unpause().notice: The contract can be paused by all addresses with pause role but can only be unpaused by the weak-admin.
